Company Overview of Kohlberg Investors VI, L.P.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Kohlberg Investors VI, L.P. specializes in turnarounds and buyouts of middle market and mature companies. It seeks to invest in companies in consumer product manufacturing, financial services, healthcare services, commercial services and supplies, business services, and automotive industries. The fund prefers to invest between $50 million and $200 million of equity in companies with revenues between $100 million and $500 million, enterprise values between $100 million and $500 million, and EBITDA between $20 million and $100 million. Kohlberg Investors V is comprised of Kohlberg Investors VI, L.P., the main fund and parallel funds, Kohlberg TE Investors VI, L.P., Kohlberg Partners VI, L.P., ...
Kohlberg Investors VI, L.P. specializes in turnarounds and buyouts of middle market and mature companies. It seeks to invest in companies in consumer product manufacturing, financial services, healthcare services, commercial services and supplies, business services, and automotive industries. The fund prefers to invest between $50 million and $200 million of equity in companies with revenues between $100 million and $500 million, enterprise values between $100 million and $500 million, and EBITDA between $20 million and $100 million. Kohlberg Investors V is comprised of Kohlberg Investors VI, L.P., the main fund and parallel funds, Kohlberg TE Investors VI, L.P., Kohlberg Partners VI, L.P., and KOCO Investors VI, L.P.
